          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Original Living Wage Act of 2017</b></p>  <p> This bill amends the Fair Labor Standards Act of 1938 to increase the federal minimum wage to the minimum hourly wage sufficient for a person working for 40 hours per week, 52 weeks per year, to earn an annual income 15% higher than the federal poverty threshold for a four-person household, with two children under age 18, and living in the 48 contiguous states.</p> <p> The Department of Labor (DOL) shall determine the minimum wage rate by June 1, 2017, and review it every four years. DOL may not adjust the minimum wage to a lower rate. </p>]]></text>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        </item>
